**Q CYBER TECHNOLOGIES, LLC.**
**Service Agreement**

THIS SERVICE AGREEMENT ("Agreement"), dated as of November 27,2015
, is entered into by and between Q
Cyber Technologies, LLC, a Wyoming limited liability company ("Service Provider"), and Shift4 Payments, LLC ,a
Nevada limited liability company ("Client").

RECITALS
WHEREAS, Service Provider provides comprehensive cyber security services; and
WHEREAS, Client desires that Provider provide Cyber Security Solutions.
NOW, THEREFORE, in consideration of the mutual covenants and agreements hereinafter set forth,
and for other good and valuable consideration, the receipt and sufficiency of which are hereby acknowledged,
the parties agree as follows:

**ARTICLE 1. DEFINITIONS**

Capitalized terms used herein shall have the meanings set forth or referred to below:

"Applicable Laws" means any applicable provision of any (i) federal, state or local statute, law, rule,
regulation, ordinance, code, directive or order of any Governmental Entity having jurisdiction over a party or any of
its respective assets, properties or operations, as may be amended from time to time.

"Business Day" means any day other than a Saturday, a Sunday, or a statutory holiday observed in Nevada

"Confidential Information" means, as to either party, such party's confidential and proprietary data and
information, including without limitation, trade secrets; data; processes; techniques know-how discoveries;
developments computer programs. computer software; customer and prospect lists, names and addresses; pricing and
cost information product and service information; marketing, operating, performance, cost, know-how, business and
process information; methods databases, data processing systems; and any written, graphic or other material relating
to any of the foregoing. "Confidential Information" shall not include information that: (i) is or becomes generally
available or known to the public, other than as a result of disclosure by the ether panty, or its representatives,
employees, agents or affiliates; (ii) is or becomes available to the receiving party from a source other than the
disclosing party or its representatives, provided that such source is not bound by an obligation of confidentiality to
the disclosing party; (iii) was within in the receiving party's possession prior to the disclosure to it by the disclosing
party; (iv) is independently developed by the receiving party without use of or reference to the Confidential
Information of the disclosing party

"Cyber Security Solutions" means a collection of hardware, software, processes and procedures intended to
secure Client's systems and data.

"Effective Date" has the meaning set forth in Section 11.1.
"Fees" has the meaning set forth in Section 7.

"Governmental Entity" means any federal, state, local, municipal, foreign or other governmental or quasi-
